        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:13PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 21 miles south of Harlowton to 17 miles
west of Absarokee, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail, along with
brief moderate rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Big Timber, Absarokee, Reed Point, Greycliff, Rapelje,
Fishtail and Nye.

Travelers on Interstate 90 should expect gusty cross winds between
Big Timber and Columbus.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
